/*
Which of the following are true about the CSS property 'vertical-align'?

<p>
	Let's
	<span class="heroWord">Hack</span>
	<img src=""/>
</p>
*/

(wrong)----->.heroWord{vertical-align: 25px;} moves the word "Hack" to the bottom, 25px lower then <p> tag.
(wrong)----->.heroWord{vertical-align: 25px;} moves the word "Hack" to the top, 25px higher then <p> tag.
(correct)----->p img{vertical-align: text-bottom;} moves the image to the bottom with respect to the <p> tag.
(wrong)----->p img{vertical-align: text-bottom;} has no effect on the <img> tag.
